docs.lead_paragraph: IOWA CITY. I AM a born, habitual New Yorker and nothing surprises me more than to be living in Iowa, unless it is that as a former Ivy Leaguer and editor, I am now a teacher at the University of Iowa. Iowa City is Grant Wood's town, surrounded by his cornfields and cluttered with the American-Gothic houses which the Eastern eye takes some months to find appealing.

headline.main: Metamorphosis of The Campus Radical; Campus radical

docs.abstract: J Leggett article on some of the trends in student activism at Iowa Univ from the student strike in May '70 to now; some current activities discussed; illus
